headlines.description: — Frank Jackson scored 20 points, including a tiebreaking baseline drive in the final minute, lifting the Detroit Pistons to a 109-105 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late baskets from Jacksons lead Pistons over Cavs, 109-105

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 29 points and nine rebounds, and the Chicago Bulls held off the Boston Celtics 102-96 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic scores 29, Bulls snap Celtics' 6-game streak, 102-96

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry hit 10 3-pointers and scored 49 points to extend his sizzling stretch, leading the Golden State Warriors to a 107-96 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry hits 10 3s, scores 49 in Warriors' win in Philly

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Derrick White and Jakob Poeltl took advantage of their early mismatches by delivering a quick knockout punch and leading the San Antonio Spurs to a 109-94 victory over short-handed Indiana on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: White's fast start helps lead San Antonio past Pacers 109-94

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat were missing their three leading scorers, and still had more than enough to get past the Houston Rockets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat run away in 2nd half, roll past Rockets 113-91

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 30 points, Davis Bertans was made six 3-pointers in his return from paternity leave, and the Washington Wizards beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 119-107 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal, Bertans lift Wizards past Thunder for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Devin Booker made a free throw with 0.3 seconds left after getting fouled on a jump shot to give the Phoenix Suns a 128-127 overtime victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns edge Bucks 128-127 after foul in final second of OT
Jokic's 47 leads Nuggets over Grizzlies 139-137 in 2 OTs

events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 22 points, Joe Ingles added 21 with five 3-pointers and the Utah Jazz beat the Los Angeles Lakers 111-97 Monday night, splitting their series with the defending NBA champs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz avenge loss with 111-97 win over Lakers in rematch
